STOCK EXCHANGE
MANAGEMENT
SYSTEM
What is a stock exchange
management system?
The Stock exchange management system refers to the system and processes to
manage an organization’s stock with the involvement of a Technology system.
The stock exchange represents the key institution for the development of the capital
market of any country.
It is also called a secondary market.
The stock exchange often functions as a continuous auction market with buyers and
sellers consummating transactions by using the electronic trading platform.
Importance :
Formation of capital
Inspiring savings
Improving living standard
Safety of investment
Strong economic base
Proper utilization of savings
Ready market
Cryptocurrency
Cryptocurrency is a new kind of internet money.
You can use it to buy things online and send them instantly to other users anywhere in
the world.
Need nothing more than a smartphone and an internet connection.
As well as functioning as a new type of internet money, cryptocurrency is also a very
popular form of investment, with long-term appreciation.
What is a crypto?
Crypto is Latin for " hidden “. It translates as hidden money.
Cryptocurrencies don’t need banks and governments. Users can send each other money
online, without needing to trust each other or any third parties with their money or
information.
Cryptocurrency is transparent, this means that everyone using the cryptocurrency
block chain can see every trade that’s ever been made.
